link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Balance Sheet for Governmental Funds in the Fund Balances Section (some may be in major while others are in non major)
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Calculated by subtracting total liabilities from total assets and then remove any balances that are reserved (notes and loans receivable, deposits, and prepaid costs etc.)

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Net Assets for Proprietary Funds in the Net Assets section.
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Net Assets) by subtracting total liabilities from total assets and then remove any balances that are restricted for a specific use or are invested in capital assets (net of accumulated depreciation, less any outstanding debt remaining on the capital assets).

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Balance Sheet for Governmental Funds in the Assets Section (some may be in major while others are in non major)
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a balance sheet) by adding the fair market value of all investments (both current and non-current) to the cash on hand and the cash in the bank.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Balance Sheet for Governmental Funds
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a balance sheet) by summing all liabilities that fall into the “Current” category for all Governmental Funds.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Reconciliation of the Balance Sheet to the Statement of Net Assets – Governmental Funds
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce the reconciliation) by summing all liabilities that fall into the “Non-Current” or “Long-Term” category for all Governmental Funds

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds as a total of all revenues listed.
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds) by summing all revenues for the fiscal year including taxes, special assessments, licenses and permits, etc. Make sure to include Intergovernmental Revenues as well. NOTE: This amount should match what’s recorded in the Revenue section of the AFR’s Governmental Funds.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds under Revenues.
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds) by summing all revenues received from other governmental entities during the fiscal year.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Net Assets for Proprietary Funds.
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Net Assets for Proprietary Funds) by summing all fees and charges generated by producing and providing goods and services to customers.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds) by summing all expenditures received during the fiscal year including Capital Outlay and current Debt Service payments. NOTE: This amount should match what’s recorded in the Expenditure section of the AFR’s Governmental Funds.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds in the Expenditures section.
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and changes in Fund Balances for Governmental Funds) by summing amounts paid for Interest and Principal on amounts borrowed (including principal payments on retirement) and other fiscal charges related to the borrowed amount.

link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWSource: Found on the Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Net Assets for Proprietary Funds as a total below the Operating Revenues and Expenses sections.
link:reference.uas-dew-part:DEWCalculation: Can be calculated (if you do not produce a Statement of Revenues, Expenditures, and Changes in Fund Net Assets for Proprietary Funds) by summing all expenses included in the cost of producing and providing goods and services to customers as well as the cost of collecting payment from them.
